manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: About the Manufacturer Bridging innovation with simplistic furniture, Furinno brings modern designs to transform your home into a one-of-a-kind oasis that will surely assist the compact and space saving need for your home. Engineered with recycled Malaysian rubberwood, Furinno is committed to making home furnishing easy affordable, and unique while remaining sustainable in the process. Furinno Turn-N-Tube Shoe Rack Series The Turn-n-Tube Shoe Rack Series is a contemporary line of shoe storage solutions known for its simplicity, efficiency, and easy assembly. Turn-n-Tube system relies on twisting the tubes, this makes setup a breeze even for those not accustomed to DIY furniture assembly. Modern color style. Stylish. Functional. Affordable. Easy to assemble.

Versatile Meets Stylish The elegant two-tier design shoe rack offers additional space for accessories. Easy & Fast Assembly Assembly is made easy by twisting the tubes against the panels. This shoe rack features open shelves for storing up to 9 pairs of shoes. Added Feature Designed with rounded edges for added safety to reduce accidental injury. Premium Quality Materials Manufactured from high quality particle board for long product life span and durability.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This shoe rack is wonderful. It gives just enough space to hold all ...
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack is wonderful. It gives just enough space to hold all of my sons shoes. It also fit perfectly under his bed in his dorm. The platforms look really nice and feel very sturdy, and not hollow, like some products. The black color of the pillars go very well with the "Dark Cherry" platforms. They do feel rather cheep though. But this is a shoe rack, not a stepping stool, so it doesn't matter how cheep the pillars are. The rack was incredibly easy for my son to assemble. It took him roughly 2 minutes or less, And the best part, no tools needed! You just screw stuff together with your hands! I would definitely suggest this product to anyone looking to buy a small, but not too small, shoe rack.

reviews.reviewText: I really like this shoe rack, it's a little cheap- the corners of the wood planks can have tiny gaps where the laminant is coming off (not too noticable, I'm being criticle) and the black posts are actually very cheap plastic... It looks great from a distance and your getting a little more than you pay for (but not by much). Bought it because it fit the weird dimensions we needed.
